SIMPLE: ahead
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ahead
<hw>A*head"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>a-</ets> + <ets>head</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In or to the
front; in advance; onward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The island bore but a little <qex>ahead</qex> of us.</q>
<rj><qau>Fielding.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Headlong; without restraint.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To go ahead</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>To go in
advance.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>To go on onward.</cd> <sd>(c)</sd> <cd>To
push on in an enterprise.</cd> <mark>[Colloq]</mark> -- <col><b>To get
ahead of</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>To get in advance of.</cd>
<sd>(b)</sd> <cd>To surpass; to get the better of.</cd>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aheap</ent>⟦br⟧
